This paper deals with the estimation of information theoretic measures, which is a topic that falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of nearest neighbor (NN) based and kernel-based approaches, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, it is likely that this paper could also be classified under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
